full_description:
G.Skill Ripjaws 16GB DDR5 4800MHz SO-DIMM Laptop RAM

The G.Skill Ripjaws 16GB DDR5 4800MHz SO-DIMM Laptop RAM is a high-performance memory upgrade designed for laptops and small form factor PCs. It offers faster data transfer speeds and higher energy efficiency compared to DDR4, making it ideal for users seeking improved system performance. This memory module has a capacity of 16GB and operates at a speed of 4800MHz. The CAS latency is specified as 40-39-39-76, which indicates the delay in clock cycles between the memory controller sending a request and the memory module responding. Lower CAS latency values generally result in better performance. With a form factor of SO-DIMM (Small Outline Dual In-Line Memory Module), this RAM is specifically designed to fit in laptops and small form factor PCs, where space is limited. It ensures compatibility with a wide range of devices that require SO-DIMM memory. The Ripjaws DDR5 SO-DIMM memory kit undergoes a stringent screening process, where individual IC chips are carefully selected and hand-tested using G.SKILL's rigorous binning process. This ensures that each module delivers high performance and reliability. DDR5 memory technology is designed to take full advantage of faster frequency speeds and enhance data transfer rates. It achieves this by implementing twice the number of banks and bank groups compared to DDR4, along with a doubled burst length. The module layout consists of two 32-bit sub-channels, enabling DDR5 to deliver more data per clock cycle compared to its predecessor. An onboard PMIC chip is integrated into each DDR5 memory module, which improves power control and delivery. This feature enhances the overall efficiency and stability of the memory, contributing to more reliable system performance. By upgrading to the G.Skill Ripjaws 16GB DDR5 4800MHz SO-DIMM Laptop RAM, users can experience the benefits of faster data transfer speeds, increased energy efficiency, and improved overall system performance in their laptops and small form factor PCs.
